    "before": "The Belnord, Broadway, east side, from 86th to 87th Streets.\nAbout 1911.\nGift of E. M. Jenks.\n\nThe Belnord was designed in 1908 by the noted architectural firm of Hiss and Weekes. It is 13 stories tall and features Italian Renaissance style decorative elements. It features two massive, two story grand archways that provide entrance to an inner courtyard with landscaped gardens.\n\nThe Belnord is one of a mere handful of full-block apartment buildings in New York. Like other full-block buildings, such as The Apthorp, the Belnord is built around a large, landscaped interior courtyard.The Belnord's courtyard is among the largest in the city.",
